      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COOL SAVANNA (3) finished sixth over 1300m at Bendigo on debut but there doesn't appear to be the same level of depth here and with the benefit of that run under the belt, he looks to have found a winnable race. The low draw is just icing on the cake. HANDSOME MISSILE (5) is yet to break through in five career starts and while never a factor last start, might not have relished the Heavy track there. The start before she was beaten just 3/4 of a length off Chowdown, a repeat of which would be good enough to shake the life out of this. OSAKA CASTLE (6) finds a nice debut option, turned in his best effort yet at the most recent jumpout and gets Mark Zahra. MISS XTRAVAGANZA (8) is a 13-start maiden who finished fourth at her most recent appearance over 1235m at this track after she got a long way back in the run. Suited in this lineup and is among the better hopes. VIEUX RICHE (10) has come on from the debut prep if the latest jumpout is a guide.",
